\subsection*{Discussion}

Currently, the \textbf{reliability} of the four methods (in terms of producing unbiased estimates) can be summarised as:

\begin{itemize}
  \item Mark-recapture $>$ Occupancy $>$ N-mixture models $>$ Count based indices
\end{itemize}

\noindent However, given the high probability of getting no recaptures the \textbf{practicality} of the four methods is revised to:

\begin{itemize}
  \item Occupancy $>$ N-mixture models $>$ Count based indices $>$ Mark-recapture 
\end{itemize}


